Class Empleado

java.lang.Object
mvc.model.entity.Empleado
public class Empleado extends Object
Represents an Employee entity with attributes such as ID, DNI, name, gender, category, and years of service.

  • Constructor Details

    • Empleado

      public Empleado(int id, String dni, String nombre, String sexo, int categoria, int anyos) throws Exception
      Constructs an Employee object with the specified attributes.
      Parameters:
      id - The unique identifier for the employee.
      dni - The DNI (National Identity Document) of the employee.
      nombre - The name of the employee.
      sexo - The gender of the employee.
      categoria - The category of the employee (must be between 1 and 10).
      anyos - The number of years the employee has served (must be positive).
      Throws:
      Exception - If the category is not between 1 and 10, or if the years of service are not positive.
